🥃 Whiskey enthusiast.
🇺🇸 Proud retired Spec Ops Army Veteran.  Hondu ‘84, Berlin ‘88, Mogadishu ‘93
🙏 Honored to have walked among so many giants!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Brad Halling on August 08, 2021 tagging @bradhalling. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text:
Berlin with the highly classified clandestine unit PSSE. See video in bio.

Hostage rescue / counter terrorism was added to the plate of the secretive Special Forces units (Det A and PSSE) as a result of the Iran hostage taking in 1979. The units stood up, and or, operated in support of Eagle Claw, TWA 847, the Achille Lauro cruise ship attack, the La Belle disco bombing and the fatal shooting of Military Liaison Mission (MLM) member Maj. “Nick” Nicholson by a Soviet border guard.

Again, conducting this training was difficult as it had to be safeguarded against foreign intelligence agencies and the general public to protect the men’s cover and primary mission under UW.

There were no shoot houses so we filled tires with sand and constructed our shoot houses. Additionally, we tested a lot of European doors and wall materials to make sure we could adequately breach the materials without to much over pressure so as to not harm the hostages.

Why a hole in the door? Some of the European doors were steel and built with multiple dead bolts so attacking a single point such as bolt at door knob or hinges alone could mean failure. @hallingwhiskey #hallingwhiskey #specialforces #hostagerescue #counterterrorism #counterterrorist #clandestine #unconventional #unconventionalwarfare #counterintelligence #berlin #eastberlin #berlinwall #occupationofberlin #alliedforces #nato #hk #hkmp5k #mp5 #ftbragg #ftbraggnc #moorecountync #fayettevillenc #southernpinesnc #sanfordnc #charlottenc #raleigh #pinehurstnc #worldstopwhiskeytaster #socom #jsoc

node.text:
Berlin with the highly classified clandestine unit PSSE. See video in bio.

After the Potsdam conference, July 17 - August 2, 1945, Germany was divided into four occupied zones: Great Britain in the northwest, France in the southwest, the United States in the south and the Soviet Union in the east. Berlin, the capital city situated in Soviet territory, was also divided into four occupied zones. 

Unclear whether it was by design or mere circumstance, but the American sector would contain the shooting ranges built and used by Hitler for the 1936 Olympics. 

With some maintenance and improvements DET A and PSSE would turn these into enclosed ranges that could by used for both marksmanship and CQB out of site of the West Berliners and anyone else’s observations. A critical consideration for a unit that also had a stay behind clandestine mission!  @hallingwhiskey #hallingwhiskey #clandestine #clandestino #coldwar #coldwarhistory #coldwarclips #specialoperations #specialoperationsforces #specialforces #specialforcesgroup #moorecountync #southernpinesnc #aberdeen #mp5 #nightvision #counterterrorism #counterterrorist #sovietoccupation #eastgermany #eastberlin #ftbraggnc #ftbragg #americanforces #blackhawkdown #gothicserpent #worldstopwhiskeytaster

node.text:
Berlin with the highly classified clandestine unit PSSE. See video in bio.

Serving as an Engineer on a Special Forces Operational Detachment, one of the many responsibilities is assessing targets and demolition requirements as well as training the team in charge construction and placement. 

In Berlin, due to the stay behind nature of the mission, we may or may not have had access to resupply of American military explosives. The intent was that the special forces teams already working under cover, would not evacuate the city when the Soviet forces rolled through, but instead stay in place and conduct sabotage operations behind the enemy lines once they passed. This would reduce the risk of trying to infil teams once the conflict started. It also meant that we had to train with European explosive materials and improvised explosives, in the event we couldn’t get resupplied.

Pictured here is me with an improvised pipe bomb.

To this day, I feel thankful and blessed to have served with the men in this unique unit!

node.text:
Back to Berlin with the highly classified clandestine unit PSSE. See video in bio.

Working a stay behind mission as well as having a CT responsibility meant that the unit had a variety of tools to work with. Most of the weapons we used were indigenous to the theater. Meaning, we used H&k, Walther, and a few other European manufacturers.

Pictured here is my friend and team mate Rick Turcotte shooting one of the 9mm 
suppressed pistols. Many from the SF community are familiar with the Turcotte name, as Gil Turcotte, Rick’s uncle was legendary and inducted into the Special Forces Hall of Fame in 2018(another post later). Like his uncle, Rick was amazingly skilled, athletic, a phenomenal shooter, and awesome team mate!
Today he is still very involved in the SF community as an active member of Chapter 6 of the Special Forces Association.

I am proud to share these pictures of my friend Rick and feel blessed to have served along side of him and the so many like him! 

Last picture is Rick’s Harley sitting at one of the city’s check points.

node.text:
Gratitude 

As we continue to push towards an amazing destination distillery we are lining up some of the best bourbon we can find. We will present these amazing whiskeys as our select while we lay down our estate in the new distillery.

All of this is made possible because our fellow veterans and friends @bardstownbourbancompany_ceo (Mark Erwin) and @johnny.whiskey (COO John Hargrove) These men have graciously decided to work with our start up as our Distillery Advisory Partner. We are thankful for their friendship and commitment to our new cause. This is possible because of our veteran connection … veterans looking after veterans!

Additionally, we are grateful for the time and expertise @dannybardstown shared with us as we tasted thru barrels to make our selections!
Thankful and blessed …. Enjoy your upcoming Independence Day! 🇺🇸 @hallingwhiskey #hallingwhiskey #moorecounty #moorecountync #southernpinesnc #aberdeennc #pinehurstnc #pinehurstresort #fayettevillenc #distillerydistrict #bardstownbourboncompany #whiskey #bourbonwhiskey #bourbon #ftbragg #ftbraggnc #veteranowned #grateful #blessed #thankful #whiskeyfriday b#bourbonsociety #destination #newspirits #bourbonneat #worldstopwhiskeytaster

node.text:
Run because I can. Many of you know I run on my birthday. Each year I add a tenth of a mile to match my age. It ensures I am and working to get better and go further vs declining. 

I don’t run because I love it, I run because I was blessed to have survived a combat injury and get the opportunity that many did not. I will continue to run as long as I can remembering all ours that have not 
survived or no longer can run.

Looking forward to 60 and 6 miles!😉🏃‍♂️

node.text: Berlin, Cold War continued: Fieldcraft - Developing 35mm film.  We were at an amazing 160th Special Operations wedding last weekend and a friend and Instagram follower asked “how is it that you have so many pictures of your career“? A fair question. Growing up in Special Forces and especially as I became a senior NCO, photography became more and more important. In fact,  it was part of the Operations and Intelligence (O&I) course required by senior SF guys to take in on order to progress in position and rank on a team. It was even more important in Berlin. We had to have the ability to collect intelligence and develop photos to pass in the field environment. Sometimes this meant developing 35 millimeter film in a blacked bag with out seeing it, or in the bathroom of a hotel room. Either way, we generally worked with black and white as it was much easier. We would practice often on each other to develop the skill .... thus so many pictures, often, in black and white! Today it is no longer taught due to digital photography... 🥃🇺🇸🇩🇪 @hallingwhiskey #hallingwhiskey #militaryhistory #berlinwall #eastberlin #specialforcesgroup #specialforces #specialoperations #specialoperationsforces #usasoc #socom #jsoc #fayettevillenc #southernpinesnc #pinehurst #photography #blackandwhitephotography #worldstopwhiskeytaster
